oc:kn_1fa3fab9 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When any task in the 5-task workflow is requested" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Execute exactly ONE task per user request. Never chain multiple tasks together automatically. Never assume user wants to proceed to the next task. Always ask for explicit user confirmation before starting any task." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Quality control at each stage requires human review of outputs before proceeding. Chaining tasks without verification produces incomplete or inconsistent work." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_4fa85a51 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When completing any task deliverable" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never create extra deliverables beyond what each task specifies. No completion summaries, executive summaries, next-steps documents, or any 'helpful' documentation not explicitly specified. Task 1: 1 .md file only. Task 2: 1 .xlsx file only. Task 3: 1 .md + Excel tabs added. Task 4: 1 .zip file only. Task 5: 1 .docx file only." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Extra deliverables waste context window and are not part of the professional workflow. Each task has exact, specific outputs." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_73adb119 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assembling the final report (Task 5)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Reports must achieve 60-80% page density with charts interspersed every 200-300 words. No pure-text pages and no pages with only charts. Embed 25-35 charts and 12-20 tables throughout 30-50 pages. Page 1 must have INITIATING COVERAGE header with rating box and financial summary table." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Institutional research reports are information-dense publications. Sparse pages or grouped charts signal amateur work. Visual density ensures readability and professionalism." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_77391e84 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a user requests a downstream task (3-5) but earlier tasks are incomplete" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If prerequisite verification fails, identify specifically which task(s) need completion first, list the exact missing deliverables, and ask the user if they want to start with the earliest missing task. Never attempt to create placeholder content to fill gaps." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Attempting to proceed without prerequisites produces unreliable output. Identifying exact gaps helps the user efficiently resume the workflow." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_867bc2a3 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any section of the final report (Task 5)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use placeholders like 'This section would include...', 'Charts would be inserted here...', or 'See financial model for details...'. Write actual content, insert actual charts, extract and include actual data from source files." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Placeholders indicate incomplete work and violate institutional quality standards. Reports must be publication-ready, indistinguishable from JPMorgan/Goldman Sachs research." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_8fe6d59d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing valuation analysis (Task 3) and creating valuation charts (Task 4)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Comparable companies tables MUST include a statistical summary with Maximum, 75th Percentile, Median, 25th Percentile, and Minimum rows. DCF sensitivity analysis MUST be a 2-way heatmap table with color coding. Valuation football field MUST be a horizontal bar chart with current price and target price lines." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These specific formats are institutional standards. Missing statistical summaries or incorrect chart types immediately identify the report as non-professional." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a4450efa a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting Tasks 3, 4, or 5" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify all prerequisite tasks are complete before starting Tasks 3-5. Task 3 requires Task 2 output. Task 4 requires Tasks 1, 2, and 3 outputs. Task 5 requires ALL previous task outputs (1-4). Stop immediately if any prerequisite is missing." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Starting a task without its prerequisites results in incomplete work and wasted effort. Each downstream task depends on specific deliverables from earlier tasks." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_afa6117d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When user's request implies running the full pipeline or multiple tasks" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When the user requests a 'full initiation report' or 'all tasks' without specifying a task, do NOT start any task. Instead, present the 5-task list and ask which task to begin with. Explain the one-at-a-time limitation and ask if they want to start with Task 1." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The skill explicitly does not support end-to-end automatic execution. Asking prevents wasted work and ensures user has reviewed each stage's output." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ca26e1d1 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SideEffect ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When completing Task 3 (Valuation Analysis)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Task 3 adds valuation tabs (DCF, Sensitivity Analysis, Comparable Companies, Valuation Summary) to the SAME Excel file created in Task 2. Do NOT create a separate Excel file for valuation. This keeps all quantitative data in one workbook." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A single integrated workbook ensures data consistency, enables cross-sheet references, and matches institutional practice where all model data lives in one file." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_d750620b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SuccessIndicator ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before delivering Task 5 final report" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify final report meets these minimums before delivery: 30+ pages, 10,000+ words, 25+ embedded charts (4 mandatory: revenue-by-product stacked area, revenue-by-geography stacked bar, DCF sensitivity heatmap, valuation football field), 12+ tables, all URLs as clickable hyperlinks, numbers cross-check against Excel model." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are non-negotiable institutional standards. Any report failing these minimums is incomplete and must not be delivered." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_e638ddc2 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When beginning any task execution" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Load only the reference file for the specific task being executed. Reference files are large and should not be loaded together. Reference files: task1-company-research.md, task2-financial-modeling.md, task3-valuation.md, task4-chart-generation.md, task5-report-assembly.md. Additional references: valuation-methodologies.md (for Task 3), report-template.md and quality-checklist.md (for Task 5)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Reference files are very large (10K-52K bytes each). Loading multiple simultaneously wastes context window and provides irrelevant instructions." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_e7f26f7c a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building the financial model (Task 2)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Financial model Excel files use industry-standard color coding: Blue text for hardcoded inputs, Black text for formulas and calculations, Green text for cross-sheet links, Red text for errors. All numbers should flow from assumptions — change one assumption and the entire model updates." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Color coding is a universal convention in institutional finance that enables auditors and analysts to quickly distinguish input types and verify model integrity." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_ef9d7b3e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any deliverable document" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use Times New Roman as default font throughout all documents unless user specifies otherwise. Use professional formatting with proper headers, footers, page numbers, and section breaks. All URLs must be clickable hyperlinks, not plain text. All figures must have sequential numbering and source lines." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Institutional research standards require consistent professional formatting. Hyperlinks and proper citations are essential for auditability." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

